"\u003ch1 class=\"small\"\u003eTODO\u003c/h1\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003ch4 class=\"small\"\u003eMake save an ajax operation\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv class=\"labels\"\u003e\u003clabel class=\"b\"\u003eannoying\u003c/label\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nInstead of reloading, do an ajax form post and have a notice at the bottom of the page that tells you that you've saved correctly (or not). On large pages, this is a pain in the ass.\r\n\r\n\r\n\u003ch4\u003eAdd a 'last write' index\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nAs per the last read index, but for write operations.\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nMay require a new UI to keep track of write ops this way.\r\n\r\n\u003ch4\u003eError handling\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nOn stupid things like invalid id, etc. we're currently just assuming the value is 0 -\u003e this is dumb, it should actually go to some kind of error page.\r\n\r\n\u003ch4\u003eAdd a sync tag \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nIe. Copies the html from the left into the code area on the right, so if you want to use right-click, inspect element, edit, etc. You can do that, and then save the changes using the sync button.\r\n\r\n\u003ch4\u003eHelp\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nIt's kind of balls adding new features without help; add some kind of popup to explain stuff like the 'sync' feature above.\r\n\r\n\u003ch4\u003e Add a tag filter to index \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nThe path should be something like:\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cb\u003e /fragments/tags/TODO \u003c/b\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nFor the todo tag. "